      echo "━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"
      echo ""
      echo "pytest-cov is NOT installed."
      echo ""
      echo "Coverage is MANDATORY for quality gates."
      echo ""
      echo "Install command:"
      echo "  pip install pytest-cov"
      echo ""
      exit 1
    fi
  fi

elif [ "$PROJECT_LANG" = "go" ]; then
  # Go coverage is built-in
  go test -cover ./... 2>&1 | tail -20
  COV_EXIT=$?
  if [ "$COV_EXIT" -ne 0 ]; then
    echo ""
    echo "❌ COVERAGE FAILED. Commit blocked."
    exit 1
  fi
  echo "✅ Coverage check passed."

elif [ "$PROJECT_LANG" = "dart" ]; then
  # Dart: coverage via dart test with coverage
  if command -v dart &> /dev/null && [ -f "pubspec.yaml" ]; then
    # Check if test is configured
    if grep -q "test:" pubspec.yaml 2>/dev/null; then
      # Try to run coverage if available
      if command -v dart &> /dev/null; then
        # Run tests with coverage (requires dart_coverage package)
        dart test --coverage=.coverage 2>&1 | tail -20 || true
        # Note: Full coverage report generation requires additional setup
        # This is a simplified check
        echo "✅ Dart test completed (coverage optional)."
      fi
    fi
  fi

elif [ "$PROJECT_LANG" = "flutter" ]; then
  # Flutter: coverage via flutter test with coverage
  if command -v flutter &> /dev/null && [ -f "pubspec.yaml" ]; then
    # Check if test is configured
    if grep -q "flutter_test" pubspec.yaml 2>/dev/null; then
      # Flutter can generate coverage but it's optional
      echo "ℹ️  Flutter coverage requires additional setup (lcov)"
      echo "✅ Flutter test completed (coverage optional)."
    fi
  fi

elif [ "$PROJECT_LANG" = "documentation-only" ]; then
  # Documentation-only project - no coverage required
  echo "✅ Skipped (no source code for coverage)."
fi

# ============================================================================
# Gate 5: Shell Script Check (MANDATORY for .sh files)
# ============================================================================
echo ""
echo "→ Gate 5: Shell script syntax check..."

# Check if any shell scripts are in the commit
SHELL_FILES=$(echo "$CHANGED_FILES" | grep '\.sh$' || true)

if [ -n "$SHELL_FILES" ]; then
  echo "Found shell scripts: $SHELL_FILES"
  
  # Try shellcheck first (best option)
  if command -v shellcheck &> /dev/null; then
    shellcheck "$SHELL_FILES" 2>&1 | head -30
    SHELL_EXIT=$?
    if [ "$SHELL_EXIT" -ne 0 ]; then
      echo ""
      echo "❌ SHELLCHECK FAILED. Commit blocked."
      echo "Fix the shell script errors above."
      exit 1
    fi
    echo "✅ shellcheck passed."
  else
    # Fallback to bash -n syntax check
    echo "ℹ️  shellcheck not installed, using bash -n for syntax check."
    echo "   Recommend: pip install shellcheck or apt install shellcheck"
    
    for sh_file in $SHELL_FILES; do
      if bash -n "$sh_file" 2>&1; then
        echo "✅ Syntax OK: $sh_file"
      else
        echo ""
        echo "❌ SYNTAX ERROR: $sh_file"
        echo "Fix the shell script syntax errors."
        exit 1
      fi
    done
    
    # Also check with zsh if available (for zsh compatibility)
    if command -v zsh &> /dev/null; then
      for sh_file in $SHELL_FILES; do
        if zsh -n "$sh_file" 2>&1; then
          echo "✅ zsh syntax OK: $sh_file"
        else
          echo ""
          echo "❌ ZSH SYNTAX ERROR: $sh_file"
          echo "The script may have issues on zsh systems."
          echo "Common issue: using == instead of = in [ ] comparisons"
          exit 1
        fi
      done
    fi
  fi
else
  echo "✅ No shell scripts changed."
fi

